: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 670px !important; height: 156.734px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 335px 78.3672px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 670px !important; height: 156.734px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="65" height="21" style="display: none; top: 68px !important; left: 44px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-justify-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-679023" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p class="p1">Hey there, SkinTalks readers! My name is Brittney, and I am a skincare specialist at Korean Skincare. I am a passionate and dedicated graduate cosmetologist. I enjoyed doing this, but I was very curious about how the skin care world worked behind the scenes. That's when I found Korean Skincare! In this blog you will get to know me better, I will answer some personal related skin care questions but first, let me introduce <span style="background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);">something new on our website</span>!</p></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" id="r-1679403978807" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679403978807" style="float: none; margin: auto; display: block;" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_col-lg-12 gf_column" id="c-1596783587877" data-id="1596783587877"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679403978794" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679403978794" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label=